The content of the course is the work of master students on their individual research topic or research project, including work with literature and presentation of their results on scientific seminars and conferences, and lissening of regular scientific seminars in the faculty. The credits are given during the 2-year study period according to the results.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of this course is to introduce master students to the research results of their specialty, but also to neighboring specialties, as well as various theoretical and methodological problems of wider interest. In addition, the course develops your master's thesis, reasoning skills, and scientific presentation. Students gain experience in the correct and engaging presentation of their research, both as articles and as presentations.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student having passed the subject: 1. Is able to prepare and present the results of his / her research both orally and in writing and to develop scientific discussion in his / her specialty; 2. Knows the general rules of writing articles and is able to produce a scientific article based on his / her data; 3. The student will be familiar with the main programs and technical tools used for writing presentations and writing articles. 4. Knows the guidelines and vocabulary for writing articles in various scientific journals. 5. Can orientate himself / herself in the scientific literature and critically evaluate previously published data in the context of his / her research. 5. Can understand and present scientific results published by others.
